WEBVTT

00:01.042 --> 00:03.378
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

00:23.523 --> 00:25.025
-Morning, Diane.
-Hi, Greg.

00:25.567 --> 00:27.193
(MUSIC FADES)

00:27.402 --> 00:30.447
-You... you want me to make the coffee?
-No, I got it.

00:31.823 --> 00:35.452
That's... that's a very typical response
to my brewing offers. (CHUCKLES)

00:36.369 --> 00:37.829
-JILL: Hi.
-Hi, Jill.

00:40.749 --> 00:46.921
Well, uh... welcome back,
if that's not inappropriate. (CHUCKLES)

00:47.714 --> 00:48.715
Um...

00:54.596 --> 00:55.680
I did that.

00:57.348 --> 00:58.349
Gotta start somewhere.

01:02.353 --> 01:03.980
(CRIES)

01:05.398 --> 01:08.526
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:10.528 --> 01:11.529
Thanks.

01:15.617 --> 01:16.659
Squad's upstairs?

01:18.161 --> 01:20.163
-Yeah, what do you need?
-I'm assigned up there.

01:21.581 --> 01:22.624
Me, too.

01:24.167 --> 01:26.503
So that's what the 14-year-olds
are wearing now?

01:27.087 --> 01:28.630
Yeah, me and all my pals.

01:31.341 --> 01:32.550
ANDY: Andy Sipowicz.

01:32.967 --> 01:34.886
DANNY: Danny Sorenson.
How's it going, Andy?

01:36.304 --> 01:37.806
Boss is Arthur Fancy.

01:38.640 --> 01:39.724
Good. Thanks.

01:48.191 --> 01:52.570
This is Danny Sorenson.
Evidently, he's new on the squad. Dolores.

01:53.488 --> 01:55.365
-How do you do?
-Hi, Dolores.

01:56.449 --> 01:57.492
I'm going to go meet the boss.

01:59.828 --> 02:01.037
(DOOR SQUEAKING)

02:07.210 --> 02:09.879
-Danny Sorenson, Lieutenant.
-Arthur Fancy.

02:11.256 --> 02:12.549
-Good to meet you, Danny.
-DANNY: Good to meet you.

02:12.924 --> 02:14.175
ARTHUR: Could you shut the door?

02:17.011 --> 02:19.305
-(DOOR SHUTS)
-So, um...

02:19.514 --> 02:22.851
-The team you're joining just lost a guy.
-Bobby Simone?

02:22.976 --> 02:25.645
-Yeah. Did you know Bobby?
-No, I didn't.

02:26.396 --> 02:28.982
Bobby was married to another detective
in the squad.

02:29.524 --> 02:31.651
-Diane Russell.
-And they were in the same squad?

02:31.860 --> 02:32.944
You got a problem with that?

02:33.319 --> 02:36.823
No, no, absolutely not. I just...
thought the job had a policy against that.

02:36.990 --> 02:40.034
Yeah. There was no official notification
to the job.

02:41.703 --> 02:45.582
Anyway, uh, Diane's just back.
Obviously, she's still pretty raw.

02:46.166 --> 02:48.877
-Then who was Bobby partnered with?
-Andy Sipowicz.

02:49.085 --> 02:50.086
I met Andy comin' up.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.798
Yeah, Andy's pretty raw, too.

02:54.716 --> 02:57.427
Actually, I guess we're all pretty raw.

02:58.720 --> 03:01.264
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

03:02.724 --> 03:04.100
ARTHUR: 15th Squad.

03:05.852 --> 03:06.978
Mm-hmm.

03:08.271 --> 03:10.481
So, um, not likely to die.

03:13.610 --> 03:15.445
All right, got it.

03:16.404 --> 03:17.488
PLACES RECEIVER)

03:17.906 --> 03:20.200
Say, you want to catch right away?
Get out on the street?

03:20.283 --> 03:21.284
Definitely.

03:21.910 --> 03:24.287
All right, let's get you out
on the street.

03:31.294 --> 03:33.004
Take this desk here, Boss?

03:35.465 --> 03:39.052
Yeah. Yeah. Um, this is Danny Sorenson.

03:41.804 --> 03:43.723
-Greg Medavoy.
-Pleased to meet you, Greg.

03:43.973 --> 03:46.559
-Uh, this is my partner James Martinez.
-How's it going?

03:47.227 --> 03:48.978
Uh, that's Jill Kirkendall.

03:49.270 --> 03:51.064
-Hi, Danny.
-DANNY: Good to meet you, Jill.

03:53.024 --> 03:54.776
Hi. Diane Russell.

03:56.486 --> 03:59.822
Diane. Sorry for your loss.

04:01.449 --> 04:05.245
-ARTHUR: Andy you know.
-Yeah, me and Andy, we already met.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.539
We got a single gunshot victim,
not likely to die.

04:08.665 --> 04:11.459
Um, Sorenson, take with Sipowicz.

04:22.845 --> 04:24.305
You a frog guy, Andy?

04:26.891 --> 04:28.434
I got two frogs on my desk.

04:28.893 --> 04:31.813
If that makes me a "frog guy,"
I don't know.

04:48.037 --> 04:50.331
-Ah, stop, stop, let's speak here.
-Sure.

04:51.124 --> 04:53.376
So that Russell you met, female detective.

04:53.543 --> 04:54.627
Diane?

04:57.297 --> 05:00.717
(CLEARS THROAT)
She had an attachment with the detective

05:00.800 --> 05:04.262
-whose spot you're taking, Bobby Simone.
-The boss said they were married.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.181
So you know, evidently,
everything you need to,

05:07.265 --> 05:09.142
why you consistently interrupt, hmm?

05:09.267 --> 05:11.436
No, Andy,
I was more like sharing the small tidbits

05:11.519 --> 05:14.230
I knew about the subject.
But I've said my piece now.

05:21.779 --> 05:23.072
Simone died.

05:25.575 --> 05:28.578
Simone died, they were married,
this is her first day back.

05:28.703 --> 05:31.122
-Take that into account.
-Got it.

05:39.464 --> 05:42.967
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

06:40.525 --> 06:42.110
(THEME MUSIC FADES)

06:44.779 --> 06:49.534
(LIGHT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

07:03.423 --> 07:04.966
(MUSIC FADES)

07:05.133 --> 07:07.176
Make a ton of narcotic busts in this area?

07:07.427 --> 07:08.428
A couple.

07:09.679 --> 07:10.805
Hey, morning, Cage.

07:11.180 --> 07:12.598
Hey, how's life with a gold shield, Danny?

07:12.723 --> 07:14.934
It's good. It's good. What have we got?

07:15.059 --> 07:17.603
Julio Diaz, shot in the arm,
says it was a drive by.

07:17.770 --> 07:18.771
Only one guy in the car.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.399
-That's all he's got?
-That's all he had for me.

07:25.778 --> 07:27.405
-DANNY: Julio Diaz?
-Yeah.

07:27.905 --> 07:31.534
-Hey, how'd you get shot, Julio?
-Oh, crazy guy in a car, man.

07:31.784 --> 07:34.954
-Oh, crazy guy you were acquainted with?
-Nah, came out of nowhere.

07:35.538 --> 07:37.832
-DANNY: And decided to shoot you?
-Must be on drugs, man.

07:37.999 --> 07:39.709
What's this guy's car look like?

07:40.042 --> 07:42.587
JULIO: I don't know, gray, gold,
I'm blanking.

07:42.753 --> 07:45.548
Oh, yeah, that... that's understandable,
'cause, you know, you're so upset.

07:45.798 --> 07:48.134
-I'm in pain right now, man. I got shot.
-Feel better.

07:49.218 --> 07:51.262
-Hey, you in the hat! How do I know you?
-What?

07:51.387 --> 07:52.763
DANNY: I've seen you before.
What's your name?

07:52.930 --> 07:54.599
-Man, I was just walking by.
-Get over there.

07:54.807 --> 07:57.310
-Get over there and get some ID out.
-Man! (SIGHS)

07:59.103 --> 08:00.229
Get down.

08:01.731 --> 08:04.484
-Have I ever dealt with you before?
-Nah, I stay out of trouble.

08:04.901 --> 08:06.611
"David Fernando Lobo."

08:06.736 --> 08:08.362
-You got a street name?
-Flaco.

08:08.529 --> 08:10.364
-Yeah, you holdin' out, Flaco?
-DAVID: No.

08:10.656 --> 08:12.658
-Nah.
-You authorizing me to search you?

08:12.825 --> 08:14.994
-Yeah, man, I'm clean.
-DANNY: Empty your pockets.

08:16.621 --> 08:20.166
-Come on, come on! Empty your pockets.
-DAVID: This was a drug thing, Danny,

08:20.750 --> 08:23.002
three guys in a car come down
on the four in the street.

08:23.085 --> 08:25.588
This guy got shot, his boys go after
the drive-by car.

08:25.796 --> 08:28.132
Spread your legs. Come on,
you hidin' something?

08:28.841 --> 08:29.842
What kind of rides?

08:30.009 --> 08:31.469
DAVID: The drive-by car's a blue Chevy.

08:31.636 --> 08:34.180
The first three letters
on the plate is Q-A-G.

08:34.555 --> 08:36.933
The guy who got shot,
his boys chased after the Chevy,

08:37.141 --> 08:40.228
like in a beat-up, uh, gold Accord.
I didn't get no plates.

08:40.353 --> 08:42.230
All right, come on, pick up your stuff
and get out of here.

08:42.605 --> 08:44.440
-Give him his wallet, Andy.
-Yes, sir.

08:46.609 --> 08:48.528
Go tell Danny congratulations
on his promotion.

08:48.778 --> 08:49.904
Yeah, I'll get right on it.

08:51.572 --> 08:54.116
-You got no friends, Julio?
-Yeah, I got friends.

08:54.617 --> 08:55.952
-Nobody was hanging with you, though...
-(GROANS)

08:56.035 --> 08:58.621
...when the sole operator
of this gray or gold car

08:58.788 --> 09:00.540
-started throwing bullets?
-No.

09:00.957 --> 09:02.208
-(GROANS)
-All right, look,

09:02.375 --> 09:05.002
this policeman is going with you
while you get seen to at the hospital.

09:05.127 --> 09:06.712
Then he's bringing you over to our squad.

09:06.879 --> 09:10.633
When you get there, I want the names
of your five main running buddies.

09:11.008 --> 09:13.719
And they better square with what
I'm going to know about you by then.

09:14.136 --> 09:15.346
We got a game, Julio?

09:16.138 --> 09:18.099
-Yeah, Pepe.
-Atta-boy.

09:18.558 --> 09:20.226
Detectives, can I talk to you a minute?

09:23.271 --> 09:26.857
We got a double homicide on the FDR Drive.
Two DOAs in a blue Chevy.

09:27.066 --> 09:28.526
That's gonna be these shooters.

09:31.070 --> 09:33.406
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

09:54.218 --> 09:55.845
(MUSIC FADES)

09:56.012 --> 09:57.597
DIANE: I don't have ID on either of them.

09:58.598 --> 10:01.350
JILL: Somebody sure wanted
these guys dead, huh, Diane?

10:02.226 --> 10:04.145
Looks like a dozen holes
in the door alone.

10:05.730 --> 10:07.189
Uh, blood trail, Lieu.

10:08.441 --> 10:12.403
Uh, past the two DOAs, it looks like
a third person was hit that got away.

10:12.987 --> 10:15.281
ARTHUR: Andy and the new guy Sorenson
are on their way over.

10:15.448 --> 10:18.451
Dust off the license plate here,
matching the partial at their crime scene.

10:18.659 --> 10:21.078
Ah, I bet you a quarter
these two incidents are related.

10:21.412 --> 10:24.248
That means the DOAs get folded
into his case?

10:24.457 --> 10:26.083
-Sorenson?
-Yeah, Sorenson.

10:26.667 --> 10:28.753
We can talk about that.
How that's gonna work?

10:28.919 --> 10:29.920
(SIREN BEEPS)

10:34.091 --> 10:35.843
(SIREN BLARING)

10:42.725 --> 10:46.395
I don't know how the Lieutenant's
gonna handle this, whose case this is.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.022
Any way is good.

10:50.191 --> 10:54.278
The point I'm making, technically these
DOAs here should be part of your case.

10:54.654 --> 10:56.238
Me and Russell would catch next.

10:56.572 --> 10:58.741
I don't think I'd get too chesty
about that.

10:59.367 --> 11:01.118
You understand the... the complications

11:01.243 --> 11:03.120
about what I'm trying
to explain to you, Danny?

11:03.913 --> 11:04.914
Yeah.

11:08.417 --> 11:09.669
What have we got, Boss?

11:09.794 --> 11:11.796
Uh, someone chased these DOAs
from your crime scene.

11:11.879 --> 11:14.548
Probably the guy who threw these shots
winged our guy.

11:14.924 --> 11:17.385
This plate comes back registered
to a Leonard Lohman.

11:17.510 --> 11:21.430
Lenny Lohman? He's a lowlife bartender.
I know where to reach out to him.

11:22.431 --> 11:23.766
ARTHUR: So who's catching these?

11:24.642 --> 11:26.185
Whatever's right, Boss.

11:28.896 --> 11:32.441
Meaning 'cause you caught the first one,
you want the double homicide, too?

11:34.735 --> 11:36.445
Sure. That... that's okay.

11:38.572 --> 11:41.325
-Yeah. Good.
-That's how we'll do it.

11:42.952 --> 11:44.704
Shall we reach out to the bartender, Andy?

11:45.162 --> 11:46.247
Yeah, let's.

11:50.835 --> 11:53.713
-We could, uh, get the canvas.
-Good.

11:54.922 --> 11:57.258
Diane and I will stick around
for crime scene.

11:59.343 --> 12:01.554
-Where's the bar, Andy?
-About eight blocks over.

12:02.179 --> 12:04.473
Maybe in progress,
you and me need to chat a little

12:04.598 --> 12:06.392
on our definitions of "chesty."

12:06.892 --> 12:09.729
DISPATCHER:<i> 5-7-2, Adam 10-1.</i>

12:11.605 --> 12:14.608
Maybe Danny will get a great promotion
by the end of his first shift.

12:17.361 --> 12:18.946
Here's one of the guy's wallets.

12:20.573 --> 12:26.203
DISPATCHER: <i>Yes, seven at the airport,</i>
<i>5-7-2 Adam. Do you copy that?</i>

12:30.291 --> 12:33.461
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

12:42.803 --> 12:43.846
(MUSIC FADES)

12:44.096 --> 12:46.474
Is this chesty discussion
coming soon, Andy?

12:47.433 --> 12:50.311
-I'm choosinâ€™ my words.
-DANNY: Yeah, obviously.

12:50.811 --> 12:53.230
But I hope we might be able to get it
out of the way

12:53.355 --> 12:55.858
before standing in front of this bartender
who owns the murder car.

12:55.983 --> 12:59.361
See, here again I'm taking
a smart-ass connotation off what you say.

12:59.445 --> 13:01.155
No, I'm not being a smart ass.

13:01.530 --> 13:03.532
But before I speak to Russell
or anybody else,

13:03.657 --> 13:06.202
I'm not going to study on every word
I say like it's scripture.

13:06.410 --> 13:08.579
I told you take into account
this girl's mindset.

13:08.746 --> 13:09.747
I did.

13:09.872 --> 13:11.832
Yeah, you did.
Just before you took her case.

13:12.917 --> 13:14.251
She seemed upset.

13:14.835 --> 13:18.047
Like maybe she was back too soon.
That's why I took it.

13:20.758 --> 13:23.511
That's not impossible,
she's back too soon.

13:23.761 --> 13:26.222
-If I'm wrong, I'm wrong.
-It's not impossible.

13:29.016 --> 13:30.935
It's not just narcotics, right, Andy?

13:31.185 --> 13:33.687
The whole job, partners are supposedly
to trust each other.

13:35.981 --> 13:37.399
That develops in time.

13:40.110 --> 13:42.988
Meanwhile, can we drive
to see this bartender?

13:45.074 --> 13:49.411
-This bartender is a shifty, devious type.
-Lenny Lohman.

13:49.995 --> 13:52.915
He'll always give you something,
just rarely what you're lookin' for.

13:55.709 --> 13:57.711
-FEMALE VOICE: Hey! Watch it!
-(CAR HORN HONKING)

13:58.671 --> 14:00.923
-Ho, ho, ho.
-Whoa. What's your problem?

14:01.131 --> 14:02.716
Don't bike on the sidewalk.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.052
-Yeah, right. I'll be sure to do that.
-What?

14:05.678 --> 14:08.556
-I... I said I won't do it again.
-Do you swear to God?

14:09.056 --> 14:10.099
BIKE MESSENGER: Yeah.

14:10.391 --> 14:13.018
Good. In the street.

14:18.566 --> 14:20.901
Any other quality-of-life
crimes you want to address?

14:21.861 --> 14:23.946
No. Let's go.

14:24.655 --> 14:26.699
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

14:42.506 --> 14:44.174
(MUSIC FADES)

14:52.600 --> 14:54.894
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

14:55.269 --> 14:57.021
My favorite middle-aged detective.

14:57.897 --> 14:58.898
How's it going, Lenny?

14:59.815 --> 15:01.609
I see this laying out before me.

15:02.443 --> 15:05.195
He buys a drink, you collar me
for serving underage.

15:05.571 --> 15:08.824
-Oh, I'm legal. I'll show you my license.
-My new partner Danny Sorenson.

15:08.949 --> 15:09.950
How's it going, Danny?

15:10.034 --> 15:11.452
Hey, I hope you don't mind
if I kid with you.

15:11.577 --> 15:13.704
-No, Andy told me you were a great kidder.
-LENNY: Yeah.

15:13.787 --> 15:14.788
Where's your car, Lenny?

15:14.955 --> 15:17.458
-My car?
-Yeah, where's your '94 Lumina?

15:17.833 --> 15:20.502
-Over where I live.
-You didn't drive to work today?

15:21.003 --> 15:22.755
It's three blocks, Danny. Prince Street.

15:23.172 --> 15:25.090
Oh, don't tell me
something happened with my car.

15:25.174 --> 15:27.426
It was used in a drive-by
this morning, Lenny.

15:27.593 --> 15:30.429
Now it's under the FDR
with two DOAs inside.

15:30.512 --> 15:31.513
Damaged?

15:32.014 --> 15:34.391
Yeah, your Lumina's
somewhat damaged, Lenny.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.435
Anybody else got a key for it?

15:37.937 --> 15:39.730
Say, you can chalk this up against that

15:39.855 --> 15:42.900
"Friends don't let friends drive drunk"
campaign.

15:43.192 --> 15:46.779
Ever since people started grabbing my keys
every time I got half a load on,

15:46.946 --> 15:49.239
I keep a spare set in the wheel well.

15:49.448 --> 15:51.617
See if you recognize these DOAs.

15:52.284 --> 15:54.286
These could be total strangers, Andy.

15:54.703 --> 15:56.997
Off the spare set being in the wheel well.

15:57.122 --> 15:59.917
-Yeah, your spare set.
-(LENNY SIGHS)

16:00.626 --> 16:03.504
I do recognize him. That's Frankie Pascal.

16:07.633 --> 16:09.885
-It's his cousin Dominic.
-They drank here?

16:11.929 --> 16:13.430
You got any suspects, Andy?

16:13.555 --> 16:16.350
These guys would be the suspects
in the original shooting,

16:16.475 --> 16:19.395
-before they themselves got shot.
-The dead Pascal cousins?

16:19.812 --> 16:21.647
You know Julio Diaz, Lenny?

16:21.855 --> 16:24.358
-Who's that now?
-Julio's the original shooting victim.

16:24.566 --> 16:27.111
And then maybe his friends
went after the Pascals.

16:27.736 --> 16:31.448
Julio Diaz? Nope, Don't ring a bell.

16:31.657 --> 16:34.952
I mean, maybe if I seen him.
Or did he get killed, too?

16:35.202 --> 16:37.246
No, he wasn't killed.
He got shot in the shoulder.

16:39.415 --> 16:40.666
You know. I'll tell ya,

16:40.958 --> 16:44.920
there's more Puerto Rican
element around on the corners here lately.

16:45.170 --> 16:46.255
Slingin' dope?

16:46.463 --> 16:48.507
Whatever the hell it is they do out there.

16:48.632 --> 16:50.843
Pascal cousins do any dope slingin'?

16:51.927 --> 16:55.556
That stuff's a scourge
I don't allow on my premises, Andy.

16:55.848 --> 16:58.350
I'm not privy to what people do
on the outside.

16:58.475 --> 17:02.187
So that would be a "maybe"
as far as the Pascal slingin' dope.

17:02.396 --> 17:05.065
I'll tell ya, I'm sick about my car.

17:05.566 --> 17:07.985
You may get a decent settlement
from the insurance, Lenny.

17:08.402 --> 17:12.740
Well, luckily I am insured.
I better get the wheels turnin' on that.

17:13.198 --> 17:17.286
-All right, Lenny. Thanks for your help.
-We all swim in the same water.

17:18.287 --> 17:20.414
While you're paddlin' around there, Lenny,

17:20.581 --> 17:24.501
anything that comes to mind,
if maybe the Pascals got another cousin?

17:24.752 --> 17:27.087
There was a blood trail leavin' your car.

17:27.629 --> 17:30.090
You figure this wounded guy's still
on the loose?

17:30.340 --> 17:32.760
And he may have masterminded
the theft of your car.

17:33.177 --> 17:35.262
So we know you wanna see
him brought to justice.

17:35.429 --> 17:37.639
-Good point.
-Take care, Lenny.

17:37.765 --> 17:40.100
Hey, it's a pleasure meetin' ya, Danny.

17:40.434 --> 17:42.269
You're workin' with one of the best there.

17:42.436 --> 17:44.354
Now you went and made my day.

17:51.987 --> 17:53.822
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

17:58.827 --> 18:00.370
(MUSIC FADES)

18:01.413 --> 18:03.207
You wanna share your
Lenny Lohman impression?

18:03.624 --> 18:05.793
-DANNY: I'm invited?
-Hey, don't be glib.

18:06.335 --> 18:08.587
Lenny was involved.
He wasn't the go-to guy.

18:08.754 --> 18:10.339
Help me with the "go-to guy."

18:10.464 --> 18:12.716
He was like the scrounger
or the supply sergeant,

18:13.258 --> 18:15.761
-and maybe he set up the hit.
-What are you doin' there?

18:15.844 --> 18:17.930
-Feel like a tack caught in my shoe.
-ANDY: Here. Here.

18:18.347 --> 18:20.724
-I'm gonna ruin your comb.
-Yeah. There's a big loss.

18:23.018 --> 18:25.312
-Were you in the service?
-Yeah. Army.

18:25.604 --> 18:27.314
-Supply unit?
-(CHUCKLES)

18:27.439 --> 18:30.567
-Infantry's got scroungers, too, Andy.
-Yeah, I was in the infantry, too.

18:31.401 --> 18:32.444
Overseas?

18:32.653 --> 18:35.906
-Yeah. Were you overseas?
-Yeah, I was overseas, too.

18:36.073 --> 18:37.658
Ah! Got it.

18:39.451 --> 18:40.536
Thanks.

18:41.995 --> 18:43.247
What do you make of that?

18:46.959 --> 18:49.795
Whoa, whoa, hey! Whoa. Whoa.

18:53.215 --> 18:54.341
Sit down here.

19:06.687 --> 19:09.189
This is big. You understand that?

19:10.274 --> 19:13.527
-Lohman giving me his card?
-Giving it to you private.

19:13.861 --> 19:15.279
What? Is he playin' me for ambitious?

19:15.863 --> 19:18.782
He wants you goin' back
in that bar on your own

19:18.866 --> 19:22.452
either for him to dangle
some piece of information in front of you

19:22.619 --> 19:24.788
or to give you someone
to like for the hitters.

19:24.955 --> 19:26.790
And the information
won't be exactly right.

19:27.124 --> 19:28.876
It'll be partially right,

19:29.168 --> 19:31.336
and enough you'll push it
for right altogether

19:31.420 --> 19:33.255
off you coming up with the lead.

19:33.589 --> 19:35.591
I told you this guy was devious.

19:36.675 --> 19:38.010
How do we play it?

19:39.511 --> 19:44.266
What you do, Danny, you go in that office,
you run this complete scenario,

19:44.516 --> 19:47.311
'cause here the whole squad
gets everything we got.

19:48.103 --> 19:50.063
-Okay.
-You all right with that?

19:51.231 --> 19:54.026
-Yes, I am.
-All right, then.

19:56.320 --> 19:57.988
You showed me something with this.

19:58.280 --> 20:00.449
-That was forthcoming.
-Thanks, Andy.

20:00.574 --> 20:03.619
This is the type thing
reassures people's qualms.

20:04.077 --> 20:05.078
Good.

20:05.913 --> 20:07.581
My only question,

20:08.207 --> 20:11.710
we ride all the way back together,
we're nearly in the boss' office,

20:12.252 --> 20:14.171
with you keeping this to yourself.

20:15.422 --> 20:18.425
Yeah. I was that long figuring
what's gonna give least offense.

20:31.772 --> 20:34.024
How's it going? Hey, Boss.

20:34.733 --> 20:38.278
-Rap sheet came in on Julio Diaz.
-The original shooting victim, thanks.

20:38.695 --> 20:40.614
The victim on your original case.

20:43.784 --> 20:47.829
-How'd you do with the bartender?
-So, uh, we'll follow up on the list.

20:48.497 --> 20:50.249
Yeah. Keep current with latent print.

20:50.374 --> 20:53.835
Yeah, we'll run these names
the bystanders gave us through BCI.

20:54.336 --> 20:57.506
This Lenny Lohman went his usual
extra mile being helpful.

20:57.798 --> 21:00.634
-Gave you nothing?
-Yeah. He gave us this.

21:01.051 --> 21:02.844
He gives us the two dead guys names

21:03.053 --> 21:05.347
and speculates they might
have drug involvement,

21:06.306 --> 21:10.852
but then he goes to play Sorenson,
and Sorenson handled him good.

21:11.353 --> 21:12.688
Lohman gave me his card.

21:12.854 --> 21:15.482
Off thinking Sorenson's lookin'
out for number one,

21:15.649 --> 21:18.402
off thinkin' Sorenson's lookin'
to move himself up.

21:18.986 --> 21:20.279
Just played a wild guess.

21:23.240 --> 21:27.035
Lohman give Sorenson the card...
without my knowing about it.

21:28.036 --> 21:29.705
He gave it to him with my back turned.

21:30.831 --> 21:33.250
Sorenson told me about this on his own.

21:34.042 --> 21:36.962
I guess Lohman figures
he can beat me with somethin' lame.

21:37.462 --> 21:40.340
-It won't be all the way lame.
-No. Andy was sayin'.

21:40.465 --> 21:42.884
He'll give you some minnows
or somethin' to get you there.

21:43.260 --> 21:44.636
GREG: Yeah. That's how they do it.

21:46.096 --> 21:48.849
You want me to call Lohman, boss,
or show up back there cold?

21:49.725 --> 21:52.602
He'll probably be more comfortable
with you going back there.

21:55.731 --> 21:56.773
Sylvia's here.

22:02.446 --> 22:03.989
Could I listen to the names
you got on canvas

22:04.114 --> 22:05.574
and what their acts are?

22:06.366 --> 22:09.077
Hi, Sylvia. I was just in there

22:09.202 --> 22:11.455
working a complicated case
with my new partner.

22:12.414 --> 22:13.415
SYLVIA: That's your new partner?

22:13.540 --> 22:16.418
-Yeah, the 14-year-old.
-He looks very nice.

22:16.501 --> 22:18.962
Although, um,
he had to be in uniform a while.

22:19.046 --> 22:21.840
Two years in narcotics.
Now he tells me he was in the service.

22:22.299 --> 22:23.759
Probably not 14.

22:29.931 --> 22:32.059
Anyways, I didn't think
you were riding today.

22:32.642 --> 22:34.853
-I wanted to talk to you.
-What'd I do?

22:35.145 --> 22:36.897
I'm worried about something
I might have done.

22:37.731 --> 22:39.775
I got another letter from Juan Suarez.

22:40.233 --> 22:42.819
Oh, one more reason
to keep handwriting instruction optional.

22:43.028 --> 22:46.198
(SIGHS) I always had misgivings
about that prosecution, Andy.

22:46.323 --> 22:49.493
And I do recall your saying that
on several occasions since we met.

22:49.659 --> 22:52.371
-This isn't funny.
-I'm not making it funny.

22:53.372 --> 22:54.664
What does Suarez say?

22:56.833 --> 22:59.920
That he was a patsy
because he was the obvious suspect.

23:00.170 --> 23:02.714
-(SIGHS)
-He had sworn to kill Genero Lopez

23:02.798 --> 23:04.549
after Lopez killed his brother.

23:04.925 --> 23:07.719
How's the guy a patsy, Sylvia,
if he confessed he did it?

23:08.762 --> 23:11.431
What's new is,
Suarez isn't claiming anymore

23:11.556 --> 23:13.058
that his confession was coerced.

23:13.308 --> 23:15.268
He's saying the real shooter
was a drug dealer

23:15.644 --> 23:18.730
named Freddy Asuncion
who got him to say that he did it.

23:19.064 --> 23:20.065
Yeah...

23:21.108 --> 23:26.071
Suarez agreeing to help Freddy out
figuring in jail he'd learn a new trade?

23:26.571 --> 23:29.366
SYLVIA: Suarez agreed
because the drug dealer

23:29.533 --> 23:31.910
promised to give his family
a thousand dollars a month,

23:32.244 --> 23:34.538
and because he was probably
gonna be arrested anyway.

23:34.746 --> 23:37.040
All right, Sylvia, you know,
you can buy five of these stories

23:37.165 --> 23:40.210
-on every tier at Rikers.
-Andy, the victim was a dope slinger

23:40.293 --> 23:42.129
who had been involved
in three previous shootings.

23:42.212 --> 23:43.255
And what was Suarez?

23:43.380 --> 23:45.340
In his last year studying
for brain surgery?

23:45.465 --> 23:46.466
No.

23:46.591 --> 23:48.176
Suarez was an apprentice motor man

23:48.301 --> 23:51.096
who'd lost his job
because he took one collar for use.

23:51.304 --> 23:53.306
Jeez, I'm sorry I missed riding his train.

23:53.807 --> 23:55.642
And now he's afraid
that Ascencion's got someone inside

23:55.809 --> 23:57.394
who will try to kill him.

23:57.519 --> 23:59.729
-Aw, Sylvia.
-Suarez is doing 15 years,

23:59.855 --> 24:01.273
and I'm afraid that he isn't guilty.

24:02.023 --> 24:03.650
And now he might get killed.

24:04.317 --> 24:07.863
I'd just like for you
to talk to the detective, Dornan,

24:08.029 --> 24:11.158
who took the confession.
Just look into it that far.

24:11.450 --> 24:14.035
-The black guy who's now a sergeant?
-Are you friendly with him?

24:14.119 --> 24:16.079
Oh, yeah, yeah.
We're going whitewater rafting

24:16.204 --> 24:18.039
as soon as our schedules coincide.

24:18.623 --> 24:20.000
And you want me to ask Dornan what?

24:20.459 --> 24:23.086
Does he feel that he put
a wrong man in jail?

24:23.462 --> 24:26.089
None of the witnesses
describe the perpetrator

24:26.214 --> 24:28.258
as within four inches of Suarez' height.

24:28.341 --> 24:30.343
I'm not going to get into that
with him, Sylvia.

24:30.552 --> 24:32.304
SYLVIA: Then could you ask
if anyone mentioned

24:32.554 --> 24:33.555
Freddy Asuncion's name?

24:33.680 --> 24:35.765
No. That's accusing this guy
of incompetence,

24:35.849 --> 24:36.892
and I'm just not gonna do it.

24:41.813 --> 24:42.898
All right.

24:45.442 --> 24:49.196
(SIGHS) Maybe I can sidle into it.
Did Suarez give it up easy?

24:49.279 --> 24:51.406
Was that Dornan's impression
on how he confessed?

24:51.531 --> 24:52.949
Maybe I can go that far.

24:53.116 --> 24:56.119
-Could you do that?
-(SIGHS) Yeah, let me do that.

24:57.204 --> 24:59.706
-I would be very grateful, Andy.
-My pleasure.

25:01.541 --> 25:03.543
I've got to go pick Theo up at daycare.

25:12.469 --> 25:15.305
Yeah, you go pick up Theo
and let me solidify my relations

25:15.388 --> 25:18.517
with one of my black fellow
law enforcement officers.

25:25.232 --> 25:27.734
Detective. They're bringing
the original shooting victim

25:27.817 --> 25:30.403
-on your case up to the pokey room.
-Thanks.

25:31.071 --> 25:32.614
Julio's back from the hospital.

25:32.948 --> 25:35.492
It's probably good to chat him up
before I go stop in on Lenny.

25:35.742 --> 25:36.910
Get started with him.
I'll be in in a minute.

25:38.912 --> 25:41.414
-Pokey room's down the hall?
-First door on your right.

25:58.807 --> 26:01.309
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

26:09.734 --> 26:10.944
(MUSIC FADES)

26:11.278 --> 26:12.320
Hey.

26:13.238 --> 26:14.322
Hey, James.

26:15.031 --> 26:18.618
-(CLEARS THROAT)
-(SIGHS) I'm standing here woolgathering.

26:19.244 --> 26:20.453
Looks like you're taking a leak.

26:24.207 --> 26:25.333
(ZIPS ZIPPER)

26:29.629 --> 26:31.631
So the new guy is, uh,
interviewing the victim

26:31.965 --> 26:34.593
-from the original crime scene, huh?
-Yeah. Julio Diaz.

26:34.759 --> 26:37.345
I guess he's interviewing him, uh,
in the pokey room.

26:37.971 --> 26:39.222
Aw, he seems okay.

26:40.348 --> 26:41.641
What, this Sorenson does?

26:41.850 --> 26:45.395
JAMES: I mean, the impression I get
is he feels pretty good about himself.

26:47.981 --> 26:49.149
I guess you want that.

26:49.899 --> 26:52.527
Yeah, you... you want an amount of,
uh, assertiveness.

26:56.323 --> 26:58.575
-He's no Bobby Simone.
-No, that's for sure.

26:58.783 --> 27:00.160
-(CHUCKLES) He's not.
-(CHUCKLES)

27:00.368 --> 27:03.955
-Mm.
-Uh-uh. Bobby had a quality about him.

27:04.372 --> 27:05.874
-Oh, yeah.
-Yeah.

27:06.666 --> 27:08.918
He had a... a likability,

27:09.586 --> 27:11.921
but he also brooked no nonsense.

27:12.172 --> 27:16.426
Yeah. Well, I was glad enough
that Sorenson came up with that card.

27:16.676 --> 27:18.470
That he don't turn out no glory hound.

27:20.347 --> 27:22.557
I'm wondering what kind
of an interview he runs.

27:22.766 --> 27:23.808
You want to take a look?

27:24.225 --> 27:25.602
Well, if they're in a pokey room,

27:25.685 --> 27:27.937
we could, uh, we could watch
through observation.

27:28.104 --> 27:32.067
-You told me they were in the pokey room.
-Yeah. Then we could take a look.

27:42.494 --> 27:43.703
I mean, what's the progress here?

27:43.870 --> 27:48.208
I'm shot, I give you the list you ask for,
you sit staring like an owl.

27:48.958 --> 27:51.086
See, I got to figure the names
on your list

27:51.252 --> 27:53.046
are your chums from preschool, Julio,

27:53.254 --> 27:55.882
'cause not one of them shows up
on the list we got.

27:56.466 --> 27:57.676
Then you got a wrong list.

27:57.759 --> 28:01.096
Well, see, our list is buddies
that you've been collared with before,

28:01.846 --> 28:03.807
and I'm betting some of them
were in the street with you today.

28:04.140 --> 28:05.183
I was unaccompanied out there.

28:05.350 --> 28:08.478
I'm betting after Dom Pascal
and his cousin Vin shoot you,

28:08.728 --> 28:10.689
your boys jump
in their beat-up gold Accord

28:10.897 --> 28:12.774
and run Vin and Dom down under the FDR.

28:12.941 --> 28:14.943
How would I know about the FDR
if I'm sitting in the street

28:15.110 --> 28:16.736
with a shot-up shoulder, huh?

28:17.070 --> 28:18.530
-Name a bar you drink at.
-What?

28:18.655 --> 28:20.031
I want to check up on your friends.

28:20.115 --> 28:21.825
You got nothing to give me.
Name a bar you hang.

28:22.242 --> 28:23.576
Name one I don't. (GROANS)

28:24.035 --> 28:25.412
-DANNY: Name one you do.
-(GROANS)

28:25.537 --> 28:27.831
-Tommy's Rocker.
-If these places never heard of you,

28:27.956 --> 28:29.833
that's going to be
your good shoulder, Julio.

28:30.041 --> 28:32.377
-Give me another bar.
-The Basement.

28:32.544 --> 28:34.796
The Basement? Who's the bartender?
-The Basement, yeah.

28:35.046 --> 28:37.716
-I don't know. Lenny something.
-This Lenny's going to know you?

28:37.882 --> 28:40.552
Yeah, he'll know me.
I don't think he'll say he loves me.

28:40.760 --> 28:43.680
Oh, that's hard to imagine.
Probably he don't know you that good.

28:43.888 --> 28:46.558
Yeah, we just been making acquaintance.
Mainly, I go in to piss.

28:49.269 --> 28:50.687
DANNY: All right, in the cage for a while.

28:50.812 --> 28:52.313
-JULIO: For what?
-DANNY: For breaking balls.

28:52.439 --> 28:54.899
You give me no cooperation,
I'm going to run you for wants

28:55.066 --> 28:58.486
-in every jurisdiction in America.
-(DOOR LOCKING)

28:58.820 --> 29:00.697
Man, go out and get shot in the street.

29:00.780 --> 29:02.782
DANNY: Yeah, why don't you write that up
for reader's digest?

29:02.907 --> 29:05.118
"My worst day ever so far" by Julio.

29:11.040 --> 29:14.377
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

29:29.309 --> 29:30.477
(MUSIC FADES)

29:30.602 --> 29:32.937
-Hi, Danny.
-Hi, Lenny.

29:33.396 --> 29:34.689
Thanks for your card.

29:34.773 --> 29:36.983
Far as the card,
let me tell you something.

29:37.150 --> 29:39.569
-My relations with your job.
-Please.

29:40.069 --> 29:42.447
I'm no saint.
I haven't led a perfect life.

29:42.822 --> 29:44.365
Who amongst us has, Lenny.

29:44.574 --> 29:46.117
If I show cooperation,

29:46.451 --> 29:49.704
help someone plant his flag
in a new situation,

29:49.913 --> 29:54.000
time comes I make a mistake,
I hope for a similar attitude.

29:54.375 --> 29:56.461
So you're going to help me plant my flag?

29:58.421 --> 30:02.258
This was drug-related.
This shooting you're investigating.

30:02.425 --> 30:03.468
It was?

30:03.635 --> 30:06.095
This was drug-related,
and I previously heard

30:06.221 --> 30:07.889
those Pascal cousins saying

30:08.014 --> 30:11.059
that they were having trouble
with both Julios.

30:11.309 --> 30:13.978
-Both Julios?
-Both Julios. Correct.

30:14.145 --> 30:16.439
Meaning the guy we want
for shooting the Pascals

30:16.564 --> 30:18.733
after the Pascals shoot this one Julio,

30:19.025 --> 30:20.693
he's probably named Julio also?

30:21.110 --> 30:24.405
Check out this Julio Diaz's
running buddies for another Julio.

30:24.531 --> 30:26.658
He could very well be your payback shooter

30:26.825 --> 30:29.285
when the Pascals got hit
in my stolen car.

30:30.954 --> 30:35.250
Lenny, you tell me a Puerto Rican
might have a friend named Julio

30:35.500 --> 30:37.627
and I'm supposed to make that cooperation?

30:37.961 --> 30:39.254
What I'm telling you, Danny,

30:39.379 --> 30:42.215
I specifically heard
the Pascals say something like that.

30:42.382 --> 30:45.593
And what I'm telling you, Lenny,
I think the Pascals didn't steal your car.

30:45.760 --> 30:47.762
I think you told them
where the spare key was,

30:47.887 --> 30:50.014
'cause maybe your ride
was a little bit dented up,

30:50.223 --> 30:52.934
and you wanted to collect blue book
from the insurance company,

30:53.059 --> 30:55.979
and you didn't like Puerto Rican dealers
pissing in your men's room.

30:56.187 --> 30:57.730
Ginger ale, please.

30:58.314 --> 30:59.566
-I think the Pascals...
-(LENNY YELLS)

30:59.649 --> 31:00.859
...are where you got help for me.

31:00.984 --> 31:03.611
I feel like you can put me
with the third guy in your car.

31:03.736 --> 31:05.530
LENNY: That's not the case. (GROANS)

31:05.655 --> 31:07.907
You provided the car.
Where's he got leverage for help?

31:08.074 --> 31:10.326
-I'm no rat.
-We got to find a way.

31:10.577 --> 31:11.870
When I come up with the third guy

31:11.953 --> 31:14.205
and he gives you to me
for providing the car,

31:14.372 --> 31:16.833
I don't have to lock you up
for acting in concert in a murder.

31:17.750 --> 31:19.752
Finish with him,
I don't need a ginger ale.

31:20.086 --> 31:22.547
So how about you make
an anonymous call to my squad,

31:22.922 --> 31:26.676
ask for the next detective who's catching,
and tell her where to find this third guy,

31:26.843 --> 31:29.053
but don't tell her
he's connected with our case.

31:29.345 --> 31:31.681
Just say you saw a guy look like
he'd been shot.

31:31.806 --> 31:34.350
-Tell her where to pick him up.
-LENNY: Danny, you're assuming I know

31:34.434 --> 31:37.186
-where this third guy would be.
-Yeah, I'm making that assumption.

31:37.520 --> 31:40.648
-Then I'll be right with you guys?
-Right as snow on Christmas.

31:40.857 --> 31:42.609
(LENNY GROANS)

31:48.573 --> 31:50.700
-(CLEARS THROAT)
-(CLATTERING)

31:51.618 --> 31:53.661
(PHONE KEYS TAPPING)

31:54.412 --> 31:56.247
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

32:06.799 --> 32:07.926
(MUSIC FADES)

32:08.134 --> 32:10.428
Good, now I've got
four detectives on a bum steer.

32:20.772 --> 32:22.941
-JILL: I've got him.
-What's your name?

32:23.066 --> 32:24.943
-Tommy Cianfrocco.
-How'd you get hurt, Tommy?

32:25.109 --> 32:27.820
-Not with the Pascals.
-Not with the Pascals.

32:27.987 --> 32:29.364
I have nothing to do with that.

32:29.572 --> 32:32.116
(CHUCKLES) I can't believe it.
This one's his, too.

32:32.283 --> 32:33.660
It's not his unless he asks for it.

32:33.785 --> 32:36.120
And it won't get light out
unless the sun comes up.

32:37.789 --> 32:38.957
My ears are burning.

32:41.334 --> 32:42.919
-You got him?
-JILL: Yeah, I got him.

32:43.795 --> 32:45.964
Yeah, we got him. For now.

32:54.055 --> 32:56.432
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

33:02.730 --> 33:03.898
(MUSIC FADES)

33:04.023 --> 33:07.026
TOMMY: This is like a nightmare.
I'm shot driving merely with my friends.

33:07.235 --> 33:08.861
JILL: How'd it all happen, Tommy?

33:09.195 --> 33:12.490
All I can imagine, Dominic, Frankie,
and I get mistook for other people.

33:12.657 --> 33:14.784
Everyone mistook you?
The shooters that got you

33:14.867 --> 33:17.245
and all the eyewitnesses
where this other guy got shot?

33:17.370 --> 33:20.206
I'm not saying this don't look bad
or I'm not willing to cooperate.

33:20.331 --> 33:23.376
When you're done talking to the boss,
Tommy will be in interview three.

33:27.630 --> 33:29.882
-Hey, Dornan.
-Sipowicz.

33:30.633 --> 33:33.594
-Got to talk to this guy for my wife.
-Danny Sorenson, Sarge.

33:33.720 --> 33:36.055
-Yeah, Danny Sorenson.
-Yeah, Bill Dornan.

33:36.556 --> 33:39.308
-Your wife?
-Come on. We'll talk in the coffee room.

33:40.059 --> 33:43.146
-Got a meeting I got to get to.
-Yeah, this won't take long.

33:43.855 --> 33:46.190
-Sorry about your partner.
-Appreciate that.

33:48.443 --> 33:49.610
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

33:53.364 --> 33:56.367
Wounded guy Russell grabbed up,
he looks good for being the third man

33:56.492 --> 33:57.744
who shot Julio Diaz, Boss.

33:59.078 --> 34:00.663
Off that anonymous phone tip.

34:01.748 --> 34:03.249
Name's Tommy Cianfrocco.

34:03.958 --> 34:06.377
He looks good for being in the car
with the Pascal cousins.

34:07.795 --> 34:09.672
That would make it part
of your investigation.

34:10.339 --> 34:12.383
Shall I tell Russell
you want the interview?

34:14.802 --> 34:16.596
Actually, being we're on an upper floor,

34:16.679 --> 34:18.765
I'd like to avoid jumping
the same detective's case

34:18.890 --> 34:20.099
twice in my first shift.

34:22.435 --> 34:24.353
I'll have Diane talk to the guy.

34:25.396 --> 34:27.523
They're in interview three,
wherever the hell that is.

34:27.648 --> 34:30.902
(CHUCKLES) Andy say he was
expecting Sergeant Dornan?

34:31.194 --> 34:32.987
No, I don't know what that's about.

34:38.785 --> 34:40.620
ANDY: (CLEARS THROAT)
So before your promotion,

34:40.787 --> 34:43.081
when you were just a lowly detective,

34:43.206 --> 34:47.251
you collared a guy for a homicide,
uh, named Juan Suarez.

34:48.002 --> 34:51.172
Yeah, he shot a guy in front of a bodega.
Got 15 years.

34:51.380 --> 34:53.174
How well do you remember that case?

34:54.258 --> 34:57.095
-Why do you want to know?
-Keep the domestic tranquillity.

34:57.595 --> 35:01.140
My wife's Sylvia Costas.
She's the ADA prosecuted the case.

35:01.557 --> 35:04.435
Yeah, I remember who prosecuted the case.
When'd she get married to you?

35:05.269 --> 35:07.438
Dornan, I swear to God,
I got no axe to grind here.

35:07.522 --> 35:11.275
It's just Sylvia's got the idea
that maybe this Suarez was a patsy.

35:11.359 --> 35:14.028
-Didn't actually do the shooting.
-Got an idea a little late.

35:14.195 --> 35:16.531
Suarez is writing her letters from prison.

35:16.781 --> 35:19.200
He's got her persuaded
that he was bought to take the rap

35:19.283 --> 35:22.453
off him being brothers
with the guy that the DOA hit.

35:23.830 --> 35:27.583
How about he did it off the same motive?
DOA had murdered his brother?

35:28.000 --> 35:30.920
He's peddling the DOA was murdered
over slinging drugs.

35:31.129 --> 35:34.966
The dealers that did it come to him
offering him money if he'd take the fall.

35:35.133 --> 35:37.468
He gave it up tough. Are you saying
I should've talked him out of it?

35:37.552 --> 35:39.470
ANDY: No, I'm not,
and I'm not saying you should've

35:39.595 --> 35:41.013
thrown back a ground ball clearance.

35:41.430 --> 35:44.934
I'm only asking if,
in the light of these reservations,

35:45.059 --> 35:46.185
do you think it's possible

35:46.269 --> 35:49.021
that maybe this Suarez's confession
was bought?

35:49.480 --> 35:50.940
Want me to say that
to keep your wife happy?

35:52.483 --> 35:54.402
I want you to say it if, looking back,

35:54.527 --> 35:57.071
you think maybe this guy
gave it up too easy.

35:57.238 --> 35:58.406
How would I know that?

35:58.698 --> 36:01.784
(SIGHS) For example, between you, me,
and the doorpost,

36:01.868 --> 36:05.037
what kind of tune-up did you give him
before he confessed?

36:05.288 --> 36:08.291
-What kind of tune-up?
-Oh, for God sakes, Dornan.

36:08.875 --> 36:10.960
Did you and me build up
some big personal trust

36:11.043 --> 36:14.046
-I've forgotten about?
-I'm asking you one cop to another.

36:14.714 --> 36:15.965
One cop to another.

36:16.883 --> 36:18.009
You being the cop.

36:18.718 --> 36:20.386
When I'm walking into
the courthouse building,

36:20.469 --> 36:21.721
testifying on another case,

36:21.888 --> 36:24.473
you were walking out.
You saw a black man panhandling.

36:24.891 --> 36:28.561
You ask him if he was raising money
for the United Negro Pizza Fund.

36:29.562 --> 36:32.732
-How long ago did that happen?
-Six and half years.

36:33.107 --> 36:37.028
So if I apologize for offending you
six and half years ago,

36:37.153 --> 36:39.113
when I didn't even know you were
in the city limits,

36:39.488 --> 36:41.199
with that good memory you got,

36:41.407 --> 36:43.159
do you think that you could
give me the courtesy

36:43.242 --> 36:45.828
of a straight answer
on this guy's confession?

36:45.912 --> 36:47.538
Even if it makes it look like I messed up?

36:47.622 --> 36:49.957
It's not going to make you look
like you messed up.

36:50.124 --> 36:51.792
How's it going to make you look like that

36:52.043 --> 36:55.171
if this information didn't surface
till three years later?

36:57.798 --> 36:59.717
This confession seemed
very credible to me.

36:59.967 --> 37:03.346
-Fine. That's the public position.
-It's my position, period.

37:04.597 --> 37:06.807
His confession seemed credible.
That's why I went forward.

37:09.560 --> 37:11.062
Anyway, you got a meeting to get to.

37:12.521 --> 37:13.856
Thanks for taking the time.

37:15.191 --> 37:16.567
Both on the same job.

37:22.448 --> 37:26.285
(FUNKY RETRO MUSIC PLAYING)

37:33.626 --> 37:34.877
(MUSIC FADES)

37:35.044 --> 37:36.837
-Hi.
-(DOOR SHUTS)

37:36.921 --> 37:39.298
-Hi.
-How's the little guy?

37:40.841 --> 37:43.928
-Oh. Theo's got a fever.
-How high?

37:45.346 --> 37:47.765
101. He had a vaccination yesterday,

37:47.932 --> 37:50.351
and Dr. Melman thinks
that he may be reacting to that.

37:50.851 --> 37:53.062
So there's no medicine
you need him to swallow?

37:53.354 --> 37:56.190
(CHUCKLES) Andy, you trying
to make him laugh

37:56.399 --> 37:59.819
with your stupid singing
so I can shove medicine down his throat

37:59.944 --> 38:01.862
could have repercussions
when he grows up.

38:02.488 --> 38:05.866
So when he's an adult
and he hears "When Irish Eyes Are Smiling"

38:05.992 --> 38:08.536
he's going to punch the singer
in the nose, and don't know why?

38:08.869 --> 38:10.413
(LAUGHS)

38:22.174 --> 38:24.802
Anyways, on your interest
in that Suarez case,

38:25.428 --> 38:27.179
I did talk to Bill Dornan.

38:28.180 --> 38:29.307
What'd he tell you about it?

38:29.890 --> 38:33.185
Uh, I wish I could give you a better
sense on that, Sylvia...

38:33.602 --> 38:35.062
(CLEARS THROAT) ...but, uh...

38:35.354 --> 38:38.607
(SIGHS) Whatever Dornan thinks...
(CHUCKLES)

38:38.816 --> 38:40.318
...he just ain't telling me.

38:44.822 --> 38:45.906
SYLVIA: Okay.

38:51.954 --> 38:56.876
(SIGHS) I, uh, went around
with him on it, and, A,

38:57.626 --> 39:00.796
the guy just don't trust me that much,
and, B,

39:01.005 --> 39:05.051
even if he did, you got to understand
that, uh, cop's figure

39:05.551 --> 39:08.804
the small chance a guy didn't do something
on something he's locked up for,

39:08.888 --> 39:11.640
nine times out of ten
there's something else that he did do

39:11.849 --> 39:13.976
that he should've been locked up for
and he wasn't.

39:15.978 --> 39:18.647
You reopened the Coleman case
and worked to get him cleared.

39:19.190 --> 39:23.444
(CHUCKLES) I reopened the Coleman case
not out of no keen sense of justice,

39:23.736 --> 39:25.988
Sylvia, I did it
because I just stopped drinking

39:26.072 --> 39:28.908
and I was hypersensitive
and I... I didn't want nobody,

39:28.991 --> 39:33.329
even if they were skells,
thinking that I gave them a bum shake.

39:39.168 --> 39:40.169
(SIGHS)

39:41.879 --> 39:44.465
If you want me to, Sylvia,
I... I'll look into it further.

39:44.965 --> 39:47.134
I'm looking into it further
whether you do or not.

39:47.510 --> 39:49.345
Fine. Good. Two heads
are better than one.

39:49.470 --> 39:52.014
-Mm-hmm.
-(ANDY SIGHS)

39:53.349 --> 39:55.393
Unless they're on the same person.

39:58.062 --> 39:59.105
(CHUCKLES)

40:00.648 --> 40:03.442
-Thank you, Andy.
-You're welcome.

40:08.197 --> 40:09.824
SYLVIA: How do you like
your new partner?

40:13.744 --> 40:15.413
(SIGHS)

40:23.295 --> 40:26.924
He, uh, he... he's got a lot on the ball.

40:28.676 --> 40:33.305
-Russell, of course, has her reservations.
-Yeah, I expect she would.

40:33.931 --> 40:36.016
Yeah. These circumstances...

40:36.892 --> 40:40.229
with Bobby passing,
she'd have reservations

40:40.354 --> 40:42.773
him being replaced by Sherlock Holmes.

40:43.315 --> 40:47.069
Which, there's no need yet,
confusing this guy with him anyway.

40:51.198 --> 40:52.324
I'll tell you, though...

40:54.285 --> 40:56.745
certain traits remind me of Andy Jr.

40:57.663 --> 41:00.875
If he reminds you of Andy Jr.
he doesn't have to be Sherlock Holmes.

41:02.751 --> 41:06.964
Just some superficial traits, you know,
like, he gets this...

41:07.256 --> 41:10.718
this half-troublemaker grin,
it reminds me of him.

41:11.385 --> 41:15.514
(SIGHS) You want to know
if they're fundamental.

41:24.565 --> 41:28.736
None of that's decided yet,
like this whole Suarez matter.

41:39.163 --> 41:41.540
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

41:50.549 --> 41:52.051
Sorry, I forgot to lock it.

41:52.760 --> 41:53.886
(MUSIC FADES)

41:54.553 --> 41:55.888
Any progress on that mutt?

41:57.389 --> 41:58.933
He can't give it up fast enough.

41:59.934 --> 42:01.018
Good.

42:01.185 --> 42:03.771
Says him and the Pascals
were looking to hit this Julio Diaz

42:03.854 --> 42:07.233
-and another dealer named Rincon.
-What's the other dealer's first name?

42:07.775 --> 42:09.693
Why? Am I getting graded?

42:11.403 --> 42:12.780
No. It don't matter.

42:15.449 --> 42:16.492
Julio.

42:20.996 --> 42:23.582
(SIGHS) So at what point
do you get a locker in this squad?

42:23.832 --> 42:25.376
You'd want to take that up
with someone else.

42:27.044 --> 42:28.045
Anyways.

42:29.296 --> 42:31.966
-Night, Diane.
-Yeah, good night, Danny.

42:33.217 --> 42:34.218
Diane...

42:35.344 --> 42:37.054
I'm sorry for your loss.

42:38.389 --> 42:40.391
You don't know anything about my loss.

42:41.559 --> 42:43.060
You don't know anything about him.

42:50.943 --> 42:51.986
Night.

42:54.405 --> 42:55.739
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

42:59.034 --> 43:00.661
(MUSIC FADES)

43:00.828 --> 43:02.496
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

43:08.127 --> 43:11.046
(CHATTER OVER TV)

43:16.468 --> 43:18.387
(SIGHS) Draft, please.

43:21.974 --> 43:23.392
You want to card me?

43:23.934 --> 43:25.894
You got any other problems with my order?

43:26.937 --> 43:28.022
No.

43:30.107 --> 43:31.609
Good. I'm on a roll.

43:42.828 --> 43:46.206
(SLOW MUSIC PLAYING)

44:02.181 --> 44:03.599
(MUSIC FADES)

44:04.058 --> 44:06.935
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

44:31.210 --> 44:33.671
(THEME MUSIC FADES)
